-- U.K. Stocks Advance for Second Day; London Stock Exchange Climbs
-- B y   N a m i t h a   J a g a d e e s h
-- 2013-07-18T07:59:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-18/u-k-stocks-advance-for-second-day-london-stock-exchange-climbs.html
U.K. stocks advanced, led by London
Stock Exchange Group Plc and WPP Plc, as Federal Reserve
Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  prepared for a second day of testimony
to Congress.  The FTSE 100 Index added 17.83 points, or 0.3 percent, to
6,589.76 at 8:58 a.m. in London. The gauge has lost 3.7 percent
since May 22 after the Federal Reserve signaled that it may
start to taper its stimulus program if the  U.S. economy  improves
in line with its forecasts. The FTSE All-Share Index rose 0.3
percent today, while Irelandâ€™s ISEQ Index gained 0.1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
